devdoc.author: Superior Blocks
devdoc.details: Multisig Wallet Smart Contract where multiple “signatures” or approvals  are needed for an outgoing transfer to take place. The wallet requires at  least 2 to sign any transfer before it is valid. Anyone can deposit funds into  this wallet. But as soon as we want to spend funds, it requires 2/3 approvals

addOwners(address).details: A method to add an address to the Ownerlist

params._owner: The address to add as a owner.

approveIt(bool).details: A method to approve a transfer by an owner.

deposit().details: A method to make a deposit.

getApproved().details: A method that gets the current number of approved transfers.

returns._0: approved Current number of approved transfers.

getBalance().details: A method to get the sender's/owner's balance.

getRequiredApprovals().details: A method that gets the required number of approvals.

isOwner(address).details: A method to verify whether an address is a owner on the Ownerlist

returns._0: Whether the address is in the Ownerlist.

removeOwners(address).details: A method to remove a owner from the Ownerlist

params._owner: The address to remove as a owner.

setRequiredApprovals(uint256).details: A method that sets the required number of approvals setter function.

transfer(address,uint256).details: A method to make a transfer.  The sender must be the owner, have sufficient balance, and cannot be the recipient.  The method calls _transfer

params.recipient: The address of the recipient.  amount The amount to be  transferred from owner and sent to recipient.

withdraw(uint256).details: A method to make a withdrawal only if there is sufficient balance.
